[Fecal contamination of the water supplies is the most common mode of transmission. It appears that person-to-person transmission of HEV is not as frequent as with hepatitis A. Vertical transmission of HEV does occur, however. A cluster such as this one suggests contaminated water, but if no patient cases are found, the source may be specific to healthcare worker eating/drinking - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4072026,310.]
